            <h3>Makati City’s Must Do List</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>1. Pray. Get in touch with your spiritual side at Nuestra Señora de Gracia Church in Guadalupe and Sts. Peter and Paul Church in Poblacion.</li>
                <li>2. Learn. Brush up on your local history and culture at the Ayala Museum, Filipinas Heritage Library, Yuchengco Museum, and Museo ng Makati.</li>
                <li>3. Chill. Relax and destress at Greenbelt Park, Ayala Triangle, and Makati Park and Garden.</li>
                <li>4. Hang out. Eat, drink, or party at the hottest spots in Ayala Center, Rockwell, Jupiter Street, and Makati Avenue. 5. Walk. Reconnect with the City’s past in Barangay Poblacion and awe with the present in Ayala Avenue.</li>
            </ol>
            <h3>Profile</h3>
